&gt; Subject:	RE: [junit] cannot run testing with UI TestRunner?
&gt; 
&gt; Chuck,
&gt;  
&gt; I think your criticism is unwarranted.  First of all, I find JUnit to be a
&gt; wonderful help and I&#39;m very glad to have it.  Second, the JUnit
&gt; classloader DOES work.  I don&#39;t know what&#39;s going on within
&gt; org.w3c.dom.Document, but in general, when the -noloading switch solves
&gt; the problem it indicates that some part of the software is using a
&gt; different class loader and that results in an object mismatch.  The
&gt; response to this is to disable JUnit&#39;s reloading class loader and use the
&gt; default one (which will not reload changed classes) that the software
&gt; under test is expecting.  Is this a bad design decision?  Do you have a
&gt; better solution to this problem?
&gt;  
&gt;  - George
&gt; 
&gt; 	-----Original Message-----
&gt; 	From: Herrick, Chuck [mailto:chuck.herrick@...]
